@startuml
!theme plain
skinparam sequenceMessageAlign center
skinparam responseMessageBelowArrow true

actor User
participant "React PWA\n(App.js)" as Frontend
participant "AWS Cognito" as Cognito
participant "GraphQL API" as GraphQL
participant "Lambda:\nget_*_data" as DataLambda
participant "External Sources\n(UBCO Events/News/Blogs)" as External
participant "DynamoDB" as DynamoDB
participant "DynamoDB Streams" as Streams
participant "Lambda:\ndocument_stream_handler" as StreamHandler
participant "Lambda:\nes_hasher" as Hasher
participant "Elasticsearch" as ES
participant "Lambda:\nget_es_documents" as ESQuery
participant "S3 Data Lake" as S3
participant "CloudWatch Events" as CloudWatch
participant "Kibana Admin" as Kibana

== User Authentication ==
User -> Frontend: Access Application
Frontend -> Cognito: Sign In Request
alt SAML Authentication
    Cognito -> Cognito: Integrate with OneLogin (SAML)
end
Cognito --> Frontend: Authentication Token
Frontend --> User: Display Dashboard

== Initial Survey & Preferences ==
User -> Frontend: Complete Survey (Survey.js)
Frontend -> GraphQL: Save User Preferences
GraphQL -> DynamoDB: Store User Interests
DynamoDB --> GraphQL: Confirmation
GraphQL --> Frontend: Success Response
Frontend --> User: Survey Completed

== Scheduled Data Aggregation ==
CloudWatch -> DataLambda: Trigger Scheduled Event
activate DataLambda
DataLambda -> External: Fetch Events/News/Blogs/Athletics/Clubs
External --> DataLambda: Return Raw Data
DataLambda -> DataLambda: Parse & Transform Data
DataLambda -> DynamoDB: Store Aggregated Data
DynamoDB --> DataLambda: Write Confirmation
DataLambda -> S3: Archive Data to Data Lake
S3 --> DataLambda: Storage Confirmation
deactivate DataLambda

== Real-Time Data Synchronization ==
DynamoDB -> Streams: Data Change Event
activate Streams
Streams -> StreamHandler: Trigger Stream Event
activate StreamHandler
StreamHandler -> ES: Update Index (Insert/Update/Delete)
ES --> StreamHandler: Index Update Confirmation
deactivate StreamHandler
deactivate Streams

== Batch Data Synchronization ==
CloudWatch -> Hasher: Trigger Scheduled Comparison
activate Hasher
Hasher -> DynamoDB: Fetch All Records
DynamoDB --> Hasher: Return Records
Hasher -> ES: Fetch All Documents
ES --> Hasher: Return Documents
Hasher -> Hasher: Compare & Identify Differences
Hasher -> ES: Update Missing/Changed Documents
ES --> Hasher: Update Confirmation
Hasher -> ES: Remove Outdated Documents
ES --> Hasher: Delete Confirmation
deactivate Hasher

== User Content Browsing ==
User -> Frontend: Browse Content
Frontend -> ESQuery: Query Documents (by User Interests)
activate ESQuery
ESQuery -> ES: Search Query with Filters
ES --> ESQuery: Return Matching Documents
deactivate ESQuery
ESQuery --> Frontend: Personalized Content Results
Frontend --> User: Display Recommendations

== User Content Management ==
User -> Frontend: Save Preferred Item
Frontend -> GraphQL: Save User Preference
GraphQL -> DynamoDB: Update User Saved Items
DynamoDB --> GraphQL: Confirmation
GraphQL --> Frontend: Success Response
Frontend --> User: Item Saved Confirmation

== Admin Data Visualization ==
User -> Kibana: Access Admin Console
Kibana -> ES: Query Data for Visualization
ES --> Kibana: Return Aggregated Data
Kibana --> User: Display Dashboards & Analytics

== Password Reset Flow ==
User -> Frontend: Request Password Reset (Login.js)
Frontend -> Cognito: Password Reset Request
Cognito -> User: Send Reset Code (Email)
User -> Frontend: Submit Reset Code & New Password
Frontend -> Cognito: Verify Code & Update Password
Cognito --> Frontend: Password Reset Confirmation
Frontend --> User: Password Updated Successfully

@enduml
